The species has two pairs of dorsal sensory bristles. The first pair is located dorsolaterally on the neck (U 
26
) and emerges from small, round papillae. The second pair emerges from scales with two rounded keels, located on the posterior part of the trunk (U 
82
). These scales are shaped like rounded triangles and do not have a posterior notch.

